new_format_lasso_data<- new_format_lasso_data %>% 
           separate(dataset_id, "_supermatrices_",
                into = c("prefix", "last_value"), 
                remove = FALSE) %>% separate(last_value,"_",into = c("dataset_name", "suffix")) %>%  select(-c("prefix","suffix"))

Explore unexplained variance on example MSA

example_msa_data <- example_msa_data %>% mutate(unexplained_var =1-`lasso_test_R^2`)

example_msa_data %>% select (actual_training_size, actual_sample_pct,`lasso_test_R^2`, unexplained_var)

example_msa_data %>% ggplot(aes(x=actual_sample_pct,y=unexplained_var, group = as.factor(actual_training_size), colour = as.factor(actual_training_size)))  + geom_point(size =3)+ geom_line()+ scale_x_continuous(breaks = c(0.01,0.025,0.05,0.1) ,labels = scales::percent) +labs(color="Training size",x="Sample percentage",y="Unexplained variance (%)", title="Percentage of unexplained variance on test set")  + scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent)+theme_classic() #+coord_cartesian(ylim = c(NA, 0.11))

new_format_lasso_data %>%  mutate (unexplained_var = 1-`lasso_test_R^2`) %>% group_by(actual_training_size, actual_sample_pct, actual_n_loci, actual_n_seq) %>%summarize(median_r_2 = median(`lasso_test_R^2`),std_r_2 = sd(`lasso_test_R^2`)) %>% arrange(actual_n_seq,, actual_n_loci,actual_sample_pct,actual_training_size)
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'actual_training_size', 'actual_sample_pct', 'actual_n_loci'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
longer argument not a multiple of length of shorter
new_format_lasso_data  %>%  mutate (unexplained_var = 1-`lasso_test_R^2`) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=actual_sample_pct,y=unexplained_var, group = interaction(actual_training_size,dataset_name), color = as.factor(actual_training_size)))+ geom_line() + geom_point(size=1.5, aes(shape = dataset_name)) + scale_x_continuous(labels = scales::percent,breaks = c(0.01,0.025,0.05,0.1)) +labs(color="Training size",linetype = "Dataset name" ,x="Sample percentage",y="Unexplained variance (%)", title="Percentage of unexplained variance on test sets") + scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent, expand = c(0,0))+ theme_classic()+facet_grid(cols = vars(actual_n_loci), rows= vars(actual_n_seq)) + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 60, vjust = 0.9, hjust=1))

library(nlme)

lasso_glm_data<- new_format_lasso_data %>% select (`lasso_test_R^2`,actual_n_seq,actual_n_loci,actual_training_size,dataset_name,actual_sample_pct) %>% filter(actual_training_size>1000, actual_n_loci == 80000,actual_sample_pct>=0.05) %>% mutate(actual_n_loci = actual_n_loci/1000,actual_training_size= actual_training_size/1000, unexplained_var = 1-`lasso_test_R^2`)
lasso_glm_data
gpa_mixed = lme(unexplained_var ~ as.factor(actual_sample_pct)*as.factor(actual_n_seq)*as.factor(actual_training_size)*as.factor(actual_n_seq)*as.factor(actual_training_size), random = ~ 1 | dataset_name, data = lasso_glm_data)

Running-time of Lasso versus evaluation time


n_cpus_full=15
new_format_lasso_data %>% mutate(actual_training_evaluation_time = full_size_training_evaluation_time*(actual_training_size/max(actual_training_size))) %>% distinct (dataset_name,actual_n_loci, actual_training_size,actual_training_evaluation_time, lasso_running_time,full_training_random_trees_generation_time) %>% ggplot(
       aes(x = (actual_training_evaluation_time /3600)*n_cpus_full,#dims,#full_training_random_trees_generation_time,

  #viridis::scale_color_viridis(discrete = TRUE)+
  geom_point(size     = 3,
